title: Delegated runner selection should incorporate live usage/quota data across providers
---

Clawq should be able to inspect current usage/quota/budget state for supported model providers and runners (for example OpenAI/Codex, Anthropic/Claude, Cursor, OpenCode-backed providers, Kimi, etc.) and use that information when selecting a runner/model.

Acceptance criteria:
- There is a documented mechanism for retrieving current usage/quota/budget state for supported providers where available.
- Delegation/routing logic can prefer cheaper or effectively unmetered capable models when premium quota is constrained.
- The system can surface enough state to explain or justify model/routing choices.
- Providers without usage APIs are handled explicitly rather than silently ignored or assumed unlimited.
